---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Tree Services Central Coast Region | Arborist Across the Coast"
  description="Tree services across the full Central Coast Region — removal, lopping & pruning, stump grinding, 24/7 storm work and land clearing by qualified arborists. Gosford to Woy Woy, The Entrance to Wyong. Free quote."
  canonical="https://centralcoasttreeservice.com.au/central-coast-region/">
  <Fragment slot="head">
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Central Coast Region &middot; full coverage</span>
      <h1>Tree services across the <span class="accent">Central Coast Region</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        From Gosford and the peninsula to Terrigal, Wyong and the bushland blocks
        at Erina &mdash; one region, several very different tree challenges. Qualified
        arborists for removal, lopping, stump grinding, storm work and land clearing,
        right across the Central Coast. Free written quote on site.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Full coverage</span>
      <h2>Suburbs we cover.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Featured suburb pages.</h3>
        <p>Each with the local tree picture &mdash; dominant canopy species, storm and bushfire exposure, and how the permit rules apply.</p>
        <div class="areas-grid" style="margin: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem 0;">
          <a class="area-pill" href="/gosford/">Gosford</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/terrigal/">Terrigal</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/wyong/">Wyong</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/erina/">Erina</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/woy-woy/">Woy Woy</a>
        </div>

        <h3>Other Central Coast areas we cover.</h3>
        <div class="areas-grid" style="margin: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem 0;">
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">The Entrance</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Avoca Beach</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Kincumber</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Tuggerah</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Umina Beach</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Ettalong</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Wamberal</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Green Point</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Point Clare</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">East Gosford</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Bateau Bay</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Long Jetty</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Tumbi Umbi</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Saratoga</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Davistown</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Killcare</span>
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Four tree-risk profiles across the region.</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Coastal premium</strong> (Terrigal, Wamberal, Avoca, Killcare):
          mature spotted gum and angophora on view-line blocks, salt-laden sea wind
          driving limb failure, and constant demand for view-line pruning that's done
          correctly so it lasts.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Bushland interface</strong> (Erina, Green Point, the peninsula
          fringe): densely treed blocks backing reserves and state forest,
          RFS-mapped bushfire-prone land, big complex removals and 10/50
          hazard-reduction clearing.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Low-lying &amp; flood-prone</strong> (Wyong, Tuggerah, Tumbi Umbi):
          swamp mahogany, paperbark and casuarina on wet lots where saturated ground
          loosens root plates and trees fail in storms.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Established urban canopy</strong> (Gosford, East Gosford, Point
          Clare): mature street and backyard trees on steep hillside blocks, heavily
          protected by Council, needing sectional removals and careful pruning.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">The rules that apply right across the Coast.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Central Coast Council Tree Management:</strong> most established trees on private land are protected &mdash; removal and heavy pruning generally need an approved Private Tree Works application.</li>
          <li><strong>AS 4373:</strong> all pruning is done to the Pruning of Amenity Trees standard &mdash; we don't top trees.</li>
          <li><strong>AS 4970:</strong> trees retained on development sites are protected to the tree-protection standard so they survive the build.</li>
          <li><strong>RFS 10/50:</strong> bushfire clearing only where your address falls inside the entitlement area &mdash; we check the RFS tool first.</li>
          <li><strong>SafeWork NSW:</strong> all chainsaw, climbing and EWP/crane work to height-safety requirements, with full public liability insurance.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Unsure whether your tree needs a permit? Council's number is (02) 4306 7900 &mdash;
          or just ask us, and we'll tell you straight in the free quote. The
          <a href="/local-trades/">resources page</a> links the official references.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">All five services</span>
      <h2>What we do.</h2>
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/tree-removal/"><h3>Tree removal</h3><p>Safe sectional + crane-assisted removal of large, dead, leaning and hazardous trees. Full clean-up.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/tree-lopping/"><h3>Tree lopping &amp; pruning</h3><p>AS 4373 crown thinning, deadwooding and view-line pruning. We never top.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/stump-grinding/"><h3>Stump grinding</h3><p>Below-grade grinding so you can re-turf, pave or replant. Narrow-access machines.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/emergency-tree-removal/"><h3>Emergency &amp; storm removal</h3><p>24/7 response for fallen and dangerous trees. Insurance reports provided.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/land-clearing/"><h3>Land clearing &amp; mulching</h3><p>Block clearing, RFS 10/50 hazard-reduction, on-site mulching and chipping.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free quote anywhere on the Central Coast.</h2>
        <p>Coastal, bushland, low-lying or urban canopy. Same-week bookings, 24/7 for storm emergencies.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
